name: Garoeda machine-head
description: Garuda is the king of birds who comes from the descendants of Kasyapa and Winata, one of Daka's daughters. According to Hinduism, he is a vehicle for Lord Vishnu (one of the Trimurti or three main gods); according to Buddhism, he is Dhammapala or Astasena; in Jainism, he is one of the Yaksa (guardian deities) of Tirthankara Shantinatha.
